<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. A. Wolf, J. Agric. Res., Washington 33 (7): 625" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="H. S. Fawc." class="Ascomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe citri" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="citri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diaporthe citri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widely distributed species in citrus-growing regions. In the present study, four isolates (CFCC 53079, CFCC 53080, CFCC 53081 and CFCC 53082) from symptomatic leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Citrus sinensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Citrus sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were congruent with 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. citri" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="citri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D. citri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on DNA sequence and morphological data (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogram of Diaporthe from a Maximum Likelihood analysis based on combined ITS, cal, his 3, tef 1 and tub 2. Values above the branches indicate Maximum Likelihood bootstrap (left, ML BP ≥ 50 %) and Bayesian probabilities (right, BI PP ≥ 0.90). The tree is rooted with Diaporthella corylina. Strains in current study are in blue font and the ex-type cultures are in bold font." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.77.59999.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/497460" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">1</figureCitation>
). The clade was, therefore, confirmed to be 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. citri" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="citri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D. citri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
